The provided code chunk defines three methods related to managing scroll bar functionality in the `DirectScrolledFrame` class. These methods include `setManageScrollBars`, which controls whether the scroll bars are automatically managed based on content size; `setAutoHideScrollBars`, which determines if scroll bars should be hidden when not needed; and `commandFunc`, a helper method for executing commands with additional arguments. These methods are part of the internal implementation that manages how scroll bars behave within the scrolled frame interface.

def setManageScrollBars(self):
        self.guiItem.setManagePieces(self['manageScrollBars'])

    def setAutoHideScrollBars(self):
        self.guiItem.setAutoHide(self['autoHideScrollBars'])

    def commandFunc(self):
        if self['command']:
            self['command'](*self['extraArgs'])
